<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Followup on Looting</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:44 p.m. 12/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Followup on Looting<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1889" TARGET=_self>Looting from Containers - TheBlack</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I suggested to Brad that certain items be marked as non-lootable. Items in this category would be those obtained from quests for certain. Also this should be contingent on fixing the looting bug with monsters as well. Perhaps if there was a way to designate a single item on ones person beyond this as non-lootable, that should be fair enough.
<P>&gt; I agree wholeheartedly with every single one of your suggestions
<BR>&gt; except the container looting. I think players should have the
<BR>&gt; opportunity, realistic or not, to preserve an item or two of
<BR>&gt; their choice before they meet their ultimate doom. I think it is
<BR>&gt; incredibly discouraging and very dishertening to know that,
<BR>&gt; without a doubt, hands down, if you die you will lose the best
<BR>&gt; item on your body. If you die again, the second best, etc. Right
<BR>&gt; now, you might want this implemented because people only have
<BR>&gt; one or two nice items. That half-elf with the magic chainmail,
<BR>&gt; the wizard with the magical dagger, etc. However, as time
<BR>&gt; progresses and people begin to outfit themselves with entire
<BR>&gt; suits of valuable, rare items, then this will no longer be a
<BR>&gt; problem. The player will be able to choose ONE or TWO items to
<BR>&gt; put in a backpack, given the time they have between attack and
<BR>&gt; death, and you will also get a nice item for killing them. The
<BR>&gt; fact is, EverQuest is NOT like any other online game in the
<BR>&gt; past, because these items can take literally weeks of real time
<BR>&gt; playing to get. A person who FINALLY after working for weeks to
<BR>&gt; achieve, gets a rare item does not like to know that the first
<BR>&gt; time he dies it is gone, regardless of how fast he puts it in a
<BR>&gt; container. Realism aside, and greedy gang PKers aside, players
<BR>&gt; SHOULD have the opporunity to preserve one or two of their
<BR>&gt; favorite items from grubby little punks who would kill them on
<BR>&gt; site just for the platinum their weapon would draw.
<P>&gt; P.S. - I know ten of you want to click the reply button and
<BR>&gt; write "Then go to a different server." I know, I've
<BR>&gt; heard it before. It goes like this. "Please improve the PVP
<BR>&gt; server, it needs work." - "Then go to a different
<BR>&gt; server BIIAAATCH." Please refrain, I will imagine I read
<BR>&gt; your post.
<P>&gt; [Realmwevaer]
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
